{"session_id":"svc-1778383421930952795","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-10T03:23:43.94806387Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-14c64797-20260510T032335-bf9c0b13","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-14c64797\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etests: replace shared /tmp/.test-library fixture with t.TempDir-scoped repo\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  cli/cmd/testutils_test.go GetTestLibraryPath uses a sync.Once package-level\u0026#xA;  helper that creates /tmp/.test-library (working repo) and /tmp/.test-library.git\u0026#xA;  (bare repo) and never registers cleanup. These directories accumulate on the\u0026#xA;  developer\u0026#39;s machine permanently because there is no t.Cleanup, defer\u0026#xA;  os.RemoveAll, or trap-style teardown anywhere in the chain. Discovered by\u0026#xA;  the 2026-05-09 test-cleanup audit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;  - cli/cmd/testutils_test.go:88-90 hardcodes:\u0026#xA;      workingRepo := filepath.Join(tempBase, \u0026#34;.test-library\u0026#34;)\u0026#xA;      bareRepo    := filepath.Join(tempBase, \u0026#34;.test-library.git\u0026#34;)\u0026#xA;      testLibraryPath = bareRepo\u0026#xA;  - tempBase falls through to \u0026#34;/tmp\u0026#34; when TMP and TMPDIR are unset, so on\u0026#xA;    a vanilla `go test ./cmd/...` invocation without TestMain in scope (or\u0026#xA;    with env vars cleared by a shell wrapper) the dirs land at literal\u0026#xA;    /tmp/.test-library and /tmp/.test-library.git.\u0026#xA;  - There is no os.RemoveAll, no t.Cleanup hook, and the sync.Once design\u0026#xA;    is explicitly intended to \u0026#34;reuse across runs\u0026#34; — making the leak\u0026#xA;    architectural rather than a forgotten cleanup.\u0026#xA;  - cli/cmd/testutils_test.go isolateCmdTestTempRoot only redirects TMPDIR\u0026#xA;    inside TestMain; if any subtest or parallel package calls\u0026#xA;    GetTestLibraryPath before TestMain has fired (e.g. independent test\u0026#xA;    binaries) the /tmp literal wins.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Delete the package-level sync.Once shared-fixture pattern.\u0026#xA;  - Each call site that needs a fresh ddx-initialized repo should call\u0026#xA;    cli/internal/testutils.NewFixtureRepo(t, \u0026#34;standard\u0026#34;) (already exists,\u0026#xA;    auto-registers t.Cleanup, uses scripts/build-fixture-repo.sh under the\u0026#xA;    hood per CLAUDE.md).\u0026#xA;  - For tests that genuinely need a shared bare repo within ONE package\u0026#39;s\u0026#xA;    run, build it under t.TempDir() in a TestMain helper that registers\u0026#xA;    cleanup via the returned func from func TestMain(m *testing.M).\u0026#xA;  - Remove tempBase env var detection now that t.TempDir() is in use.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Migrating other test packages that use their own private fixtures.\u0026#xA;    This bead is scoped to GetTestLibraryPath and its callers in cli/cmd/.\u0026#xA;  - Performance optimization (reusing fixtures across tests within one\u0026#xA;    package via TestMain is fine; cross-process reuse is what\u0026#39;s banned).\u0026#xA;  - Frontend test cleanup.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;INTERSECTIONS\u0026#xA;  - testutils.NewFixtureRepo (cli/internal/testutils/) is the canonical\u0026#xA;    replacement. CLAUDE.md already documents it as the preferred path.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/cmd/testutils_test.go no longer contains a sync.Once package-level fixture; GetTestLibraryPath is removed or replaced with a per-test fixture call.\u0026#xA;2. Every former GetTestLibraryPath caller uses testutils.NewFixtureRepo(t, ...) or a t.TempDir()-scoped fixture with t.Cleanup registered.\u0026#xA;3. After running cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/..., neither /tmp/.test-library nor /tmp/.test-library.git exists on disk (verified by a test that asserts os.Stat returns ErrNotExist for both paths after the package finishes).\u0026#xA;4. TestNoSharedTmpFixtureLeaks in cli/cmd/testutils_test.go (or equivalent) asserts the cleanup invariant.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... ./internal/testutils/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:tests, kind:fix, prevention\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"96fa0684d1c68652db878b5247b457f6835fc74a\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260510T032335-bf9c0b13","base_rev":"96fa0684d1c68652db878b5247b457f6835fc74a","bead_id":"ddx-14c64797","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13","correlation_id":"ddx-14c64797:20260510T032335-bf9c0b13","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260510T032335-bf9c0b13/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"8fa0f185663ecabd9672e53cd16fb9a89e0605e657103b091c8ec1c4f9808bed","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-17087fc2","worker_id":""}}}
